{
  "stem": "25773.6",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They saved about maybe 100 girls like that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And run across to the pharmacy on the stairs.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Afterwards, I got to know from Stefan, who joined us after the whole ordeal, that they discovered the plot and the shot maybe 30 nurses.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I was very, very upset about that story.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The Germans discovered that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we found ourselves-- also Krystyna-- on the stairs.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The pharmacy was closed to our great regret and anxiety.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So we decided to stay there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But we fell on our knees, and I speak of believing or not believe-- believe me, all we said is, God Almighty, thank you.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Thank you.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "God Almighty, Father in heaven, thank you.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "You know, couldn't-- the gratefulness was so great.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We were so delighted.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And after midnight or so, this young man appeared and [?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Masia ?] ventured to see him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "He opened the door.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And he-- he thought he sees a ghost from-- from the-- from the-- from the ground.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And then-- and then two of us appeared, filthy, full of vermin, smelling.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "He said, God Almighty, I remember you.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "He said, sweet Jesus, God Almighty.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "He just couldn't believe what has befallen him.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And he ushered us to his place, and we told him the story.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "He said his wife and his father, parents-in-law are on a holiday.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "Anyway, he gave us shelter for three days.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "For three days, he was pouring-- I remember in Polish it was called [POLISH].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And he poured over us stuff to kill the vermin.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "We were full of lice, full-- full of it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "He-- we burnt-- he-- he burnt our dresses.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "He gave us dresses of his wife.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "He gave us food, he gave us money.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "You know, all Polish people help.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He knew [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Masia-- ?] she was his friend--",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
